node.title: Victoria records 1,405 new COVID cases as Omicron exposure forces hundreds into isolation
node.description: Health officials confirm a person with the Omicron variant attended venues in Fitzroy and Collingwood on Friday night, potentially exposing hundreds of people to the virus, as Victoria records 1,405 new cases overnight.

node.title: Meet the passengers: Tears, hugs and 'early Christmas presents' at Hobart Airport
node.description: Hobart Airport's arrival hall is awash with tears and lit with smiles as Tasmania's border reopens fully to vaccinated travellers just a week and a half out from Christmas.

node.title: Michael Gargiulo Dies at 95; Documented the Moscow ‘Kitchen Debate’
node.description: Sent to the Soviet Union in 1959 to promote color television, he ended up taping what he later called a “turning point” in U.S.-Soviet relations.
